    <detaileddescription>
<para>The <bold>IADLX3DWaitForVerticalRefresh</bold> interface configures the vertical refresh (VSync) settings of a GPU.</para>
<para><table rows="4" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="no"><para>InterfaceId:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>IADLX3DWaitForVerticalRefresh</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Smart Pointer Interface Name:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>IADLX3DWaitForVerticalRefreshPtr</para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Inherits:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para><ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x_interface" kindref="compound">IADLXInterface</ref></para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para>Inherited By:</para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>N/A</para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
<para>VSync synchronizes the transition to a new frame of animation with the display update so no tearing is visible between frames.<linebreak/>
 Limits the frame rate at the displayâ€™s refresh rate.<linebreak/>
</para>
<sect2 id="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x3_d_wait_for_vertical_refresh_1autotoc_md18">
<title>Dependent Interfaces</title>
<para>When AMD Radeon Enhanced Sync is enabled, the <ref refid="_d_o_x__i_a_d_l_x3_d_wait_for_vertical_refresh" kindref="compound">VSync</ref> interface is automatically disabled. However, the state of VSync will not affect Enhanced Sync.<linebreak/>
 <bold>Note:</bold> If the disabled interface is later re-enabled, its previous configuration settings will be restored.</para>
